    {
      "id": 396,
      "name": "Hornung's Guess",
      "level": "1",
      "school": "Divination",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "",
      "range": "300 yards",
      "aoe": "Special",
      "casting_time": "2",
      "duration": "Instantaneous",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "Hornung, one of the leading wizards in the field of wild magic (before his untimely disappearance while experimenting with wildwind),developed this spell to improve the accuracy of his estimates.\n\nThe spell provides a wizard with an instant and highly accurate-estimate of the number of persons or objects in a group.\n\nThe spell's area effect is one group of a general class of objects.\n\nAll objects of the group must be within spell range and the group as a whole must be visible to the caster.\n\nThe wizard need not see every individual in the group, merely the general limits of the group's size and area.\n\nFor example, a wizard on a hill could look down on a forest and estimate the number of trees in all or part of it.\n\nHe could not get an estimate of the number of goblins within the forest, however, since the group as a whole is concealed from sight.\n\nThe estimate generated is accurate to the largest factor of ten .For example, if Hornung's guess were cast on a group of 439 horsemen, the estimate would be 400.\n\nIf there were 2,670 horsemen, the spell would estimate 3,000.\n\nIf there were 37 horsemen, the answer would be 40.\n\nClearly, using the spell on small groups(especially those with fewer than 10 members) is pointless.\n\nHornung's guess can be used to quickly estimate the size of treasure hoards and army units.\n\nIt is particularly popular with moneylenders and generals.",
      "source": "Tome of Magic",
      "page": 17,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 397,
      "name": "Hypnotism",
      "level": "1",
      "school": "Enchantment",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": true,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "",
      "range": "5 yds.",
      "aoe": "30 ft. cube",
      "casting_time": "1",
      "duration": "1 rd.+ 1 rd./level",
      "save": "Negate",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "The gestures of the wizard, along with his droning incantation, cause 1d6 creatures within the area to become susceptible to a suggestion - a brief and reasonable-sounding request (see the 3rd-level wizard suggestion spell).\n\nThe request must be given after the hypnotism spell is cast.\n\nUntil that time the success of the spell is unknown.\n\nNote that the subsequent suggestion is not a spell, but simply a vocalized urging (the caster must speak a language the creature understands for this spell to work).\n\nCreatures that successfully roll their saving throws are not under hypnotic influence.\n\nThose who are exceptionally wary or hostile save with +1 to +3 bonuses.\n\nIf the spell is cast at an individual creature that meets the caster's gaze, the saving throw is made with a penalty of -2.\n\nA creature that fails its saving throw does not remember that the caster enspelled it.",
