      "damage": "",
      "description": "Within one round of casting this spell, the wizard magically conjures 2d4 1st-level monsters (selected by the DM, from his 1st-level encounter tables).\n\nThe monsters appear in an area within the spell range, as desired by the wizard.\n\nThey attack the spell user's opponents to the best of their ability until either he commands that the attacks cease, the spell duration expires, or the monsters are slain.\n\nThese creatures do not check morale, but they vanish when slain.\n\nNote that if no opponent exists to fight, summoned monsters can, if the wizard can communicate with them and if they are physically able, perform other services for the summoning wizard.\n\nIn rare cases, adventurers have been known to disappear, summoned by powerful spellcasters using this spell.\n\nThose summoned recall all the details of their trip.\n\nThe material components of this spell are a tiny bag and a small (not necessarily lit) candle.",
