    {
      "id": 525,
      "name": "Spirit Armor",
      "level": "3",
      "school": "Necromancy",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": true,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "",
      "range": "0",
      "aoe": "The caster",
      "casting_time": "3",
      "duration": "2 rounds/level",
      "save": "Special",
      "damage": "2d3",
      "description": "**This spell** allows the wizard to surround himself with a portion of his own life essence, which takes the form of a shimmering aura.\n\nThe spirit armor offers protection equivalent to splint mail (AC 16) and grants the wizard a + 3 bonus to saving throws vs.\n\nmagical attacks.\n\nThe spirit armor's effects are not cumulative with other types of armor or magical protection, but Dexterity bonuses apply.\n\nThe spirit armor is effective against magical and nonmagical weapons and attacks.\n\nIt does not hinder movement or add weight or encumbrance.\n\nIt does not interfere with spellcasting.\n\nWhen the spell ends, the aura dissipates and the caster temporarily loses a bit of his life essence, suffering 2d3 points of damage unless he succeeds at a saving throw vs.\n\nspell.\n\nThese lost HP return at a rate of 1/hour.\n\nNo damage is sustained if the save is successful.",
      "source": "Tome of Magic",
      "page": 26,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 526,
      "name": "Suggestion",
      "level": "3",
      "school": "Enchantment",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": true,
      "materials": "a snake's tongue and either a bit of honey-comb or a drop of sweet oil",
      "range": "30 yds.",
      "aoe": "1 creature",
      "casting_time": "3",
      "duration": "1 hr.+ 1 hr./level",
      "save": "Negate",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "When this spell is cast by the wizard, he influences the actions of the chosen recipient by the utterance of a few words - phrases or a sentence or two - suggesting a course of action desirable to the spellcaster.\n\nThe creature to be influenced must, of course, be able to understand the wizards suggestion - it must be spoken in a language that the spell recipient understands.\n\nThe suggestion must be worded in such a manner as to make the action sound reasonable; asking the creature to stab itself, throw itself onto a spear, immolate itself, or do some other obviously harmful act automatically negates the effect of the spell.\n\nHowever, a suggestion that a pool of acid was actually pure water and that a quick dip would be refreshing is another matter.\n\nUrging a red dragon to stop attacking the wizards party so that the dragon and party could jointly loot a rich treasure elsewhere is likewise a reasonable use of the spell's power.\n\nThe course of action of a suggestion can continue in effect for a considerable duration, such as in the case of the red dragon mentioned above.\n\nConditions that will trigger a special action can also be specified; if the condition is not met before the spell expires, then the action will not be performed.\n\nIf the target successfully rolls its saving throw, the spell has no effect.\n\nNote that a very reasonable suggestion causes the saving throw to be made with a penalty (such as -1, -2, etc.) at the discretion of the Dungeon Master.\n\nUndead are not subject to suggestion.\n\nThe material components of this spell are a snake's tongue and either a bit of honey-comb or a drop of sweet oil.",
      "source": "Player's Handbook",
      "page": 197,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 527,
      "name": "Tongues",
      "level": "3",
      "school": "Alteration",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": true,
      "materials": "a small clay model of a ziggurat",
      "range": "0",
      "aoe": "30-ft. radius",
      "casting_time": "3",
      "duration": "1 rd./level",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "**This spell** enables the wizard to speak and understand additional languages, whether they are racial tongues or regional dialects.\n\nThis does not enable the caster to speak with animals.\n\nThe spell enables the caster to be understood by all creatures of that type within hearing distance, usually 60 feet.\n\n**This spell** does not predispose the subject toward the caster in any way.\n\nThe wizard can speak one additional tongue for every three levels of experience.\n\nThe reverse of the spell cancels the effect of the tongues spell or confuses verbal communication of any sort within the area of effect.\n\nThe material component is a small clay model of a ziggurat, which shatters when the spell is pronounced.",
      "source": "Player's Handbook",
      "page": 197,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 528,
      "name": "Vampiric Touch",
      "level": "3",
      "school": "Necromancy",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": true,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "",
      "range": "Touch",
      "aoe": "The caster",
      "casting_time": "3",
      "duration": "One touch",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "When the caster touches an opponent in melee with a successful attack roll, the opponent loses 1d6 hit points for every two caster levels, to a maximum drain of 6d6 for a 12th-level caster.\n\nThe spell is expended when a successful touch is made or one turn passes.\n\nThe hit points are added to the caster's total, with any hit points over the caster's normal total treated as temporary additional hit points.\n\nAny damage to the caster is subtracted from the temporary hit points first.\n\nAfter one hour, any extra hit points above the caster's normal total are lost.\n\nThe creature originally losing hit points through this spell can regain them by magical or normal healing.\n\nUndead creatures are unaffected by this spell.",
      "source": "Player's Handbook",
      "page": 197,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 529,
      "name": "Wall of Water",
      "level": "3",
      "school": "Evocation",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": true,
      "material": true,
      "materials": "a vial full of blessed spring water",
      "range": "30 yards",
      "aoe": "Special",
      "casting_time": "3",
      "duration": "Special",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "**This spell** calls into being a curtain or field of water that remains intact and upright in defiance of gravity.\n\nThe wall lasts as long as the wizard chooses to concentrate on maintaining it or one round per level if the wizard chooses not to concentrate on holding it together.\n\nThe caster may shape the wall of water in one of three ways: A.\n\nWater Curtain.\n\nIn this form, the wizard conjures one plane of water, 5 feet square and 1 foot thick, per experience level; for example, a 5th-level caster can create five 5-foot x 5-foot x 1-foot wall sections that would be enough to block an arched passageway 15 feet wide and 10 feet high with a curtain of water 1 foot thick.\n\nThe curtain's lower edge must rest upon the ground, but need not be anchored on either side, and it remains cohesive and upright for the duration of the spell.\n\nOnce raised, the wall cannot be moved.\n\nB.\n\nHemisphere.\n\nIn this manifestation, the wall of water forms a dome 1 foot thick over the caster, with an inner radius equal to 3 feet plus 1 foot per caster level; a 7th level caster could create a dome with a 10 foot radius.\n\nThe wall must rest upon the ground.\n\nThe dome is immobile.\n\nC.\n\nSphere.\n\nIf cast underwater, the caster may shape the wall of water into a sphere 1 foot thick, with an inner radius equal to 3 feet plus 1 foot per caster level (no air is in the sphere).\n\nThe sphere is centered on the caster and moves with him.\n\nIn any form, the wall of water has two primary effects.\n\nFirst of all, missile fire through the wall is next to impossible, suffering a -4 attack penalty for each foot of thickness as well as -1 damage penalty for every two feet of thickness.\n\nCreatures gain a +1 bonus to saving throws against attack spells that must pass through the wall.\n\nIf the spell allows no saving throw, none is granted by the wall of water.\n\nSecondly, physical passage through the wall is hindered; any creature trying to pass through must take one full round to do so and becomes soaked to the skin in the process.\n\nThe wall of water can be defeated or bypassed by a number of spells or effects.\n\nAt the end of the spell's duration, the water loses its cohesiveness and collapses, which may surprise those sheltering under the hemisphere or standing next to the curtain.\n\nNote the water itself may be fresh water (25% chance), salt water (50% chance) or brackish (25% chance), although the sphere will always be composed of the water type that surrounds it.\n\nThe material component is a vial full of blessed spring water.",
      "source": "Spells and Magic",
      "page": 144,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 530,
      "name": "Water Breathing",
      "level": "3",
      "school": "Alteration",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": true,
      "material": true,
      "materials": "a short reed or piece of straw",
      "range": "Touch",
      "aoe": "Creature touched",
