      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 655,
      "name": "Death Spell",
      "level": "6",
      "school": "Necromancy",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": true,
      "material": true,
      "materials": "a crushed black pearl",
      "range": "10 yds./level",
      "aoe": "30-ft. cube/level",
      "casting_time": "6",
      "duration": "Instantaneous",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "**When a death spell is cast**, it snuffs out the life forces of creatures in the area of effect instantly and irrevocably.\n\nSuch creatures cannot be raised or resurrected, but an individual slain in this manner might be brought back via a wish.\n\nThe number of creatures that can be slain is a function of their Hit Dice.\n\n(See book for table ).\n\nIn other words, from the 4d20 roll subtract the number of creatures of less than 2 Hit Dice (these creatures die).\n\nIf there are any remaining points from the 4d20 roll, subtract 2 for each creature of 2 to 4 Hit Dice (these creatures also die).\n\nIf this still doesn't use up all the 4d20 roll, subtract 10 for each creature of 4+1 to 6+3 Hit Dice, and so on.\n\nStop when all the creatures are dead, all the 4d20 roll is used up, or the remainder is less than half the CF of any remaining creatures.\n\n(If the remainder is one-half or more of the CF of a creature, that creature dies.) For example, a mixed group of 20 goblins, eight gnolls, and four ogres, led by a hill giant, are caught in the area of a death spell.\n\nThe 4d20 roll gives a total of 53 points; 20 of this eliminates the goblins (20 x 1 CF), 16 kills the gnolls (8 x 2 CF), and the remaining 17 kills two ogres (10 points to kill one ogre, and the remaining 7 points are enough to kill one more ogre).\n\nThe other two ogres and the hill giant are unharmed.\n\nA death spell does not affect lycanthropes, undead creatures, or creatures from planes other than the Prime Material.\n\nThe material component of this spell is a crushed black pearl with a minimum value of 1,000 gp.",
      "source": "Player's Handbook",
      "page": 222,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 656,
      "name": "Demishadow Magic",
      "level": "6",
