      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 692,
      "name": "Wildshield",
      "level": "6",
      "school": "Alteration",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": true,
      "material": true,
      "materials": "a small sponge.",
      "range": "0",
      "aoe": "The caster",
      "casting_time": "1 round",
      "duration": "Special",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "**This spell** cloaks the caster in a whirling band of scintillating colors, completely concealing him.\n\nThe caster is able to see normally within and outside the shield.\n\nThe wildshield protects the caster from the effects of spells and magical items.\n\nThe shield can completely absorb 2d6 spell levels (i.e., if the roll of 2d6 results in 10, the shield could absorb ten 1st-level spells, two 5th-level spells, or any similar combination), thereby negating their effects on the caster.\n\nBoth area effect spells and those individually targeted at the wild mage can be absorbed.\n\nIn the case of area spells, the wildshield protects only the mage.\n\nAll others in the area of effect suffer normal effects from the spell.\n\nWildshield also protects against wild surges, whether caused by the caster",
      "source": "Tome of Magic",
      "page": 39,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 693,
      "name": "Wildstrike",
      "level": "6",
      "school": "Conjuration",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": true,
      "material": true,
      "materials": "a small glass tub",
      "range": "30 yards",
      "aoe": "One creature",
      "casting_time": "6",
      "duration": "2d4 rounds",
      "save": "Negate",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "**This spell** is used primarily against hostile spellcasters.\n\nIt distorts all attempts at spellcasting, converting spell energy into wild surges.\n\nThe victim of a wildstrike is allowed a saving throw; if successful, the spell has no effect.\n\nIf the saving throw is failed, the target is enclosed within a field of wild magic.\n\nIf the victim casts spells or uses a charge from a magical item, a wild surge is automatically created (refer to Table 2).\n\nWhen determining the effects of this surge, the true level of the wild mage who cast the wildstrike is subtracted from the die roll, making the effects of the wild surge more likely to affect the victim.\n\nThe material component is a small glass tub that is shattered in the casting.",
