    {
      "id": 740,
      "name": "Demand",
      "level": "8",
      "school": "Evocation",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": true,
      "material": true,
      "materials": "a pair of cylinders",
      "range": "Unlimited",
      "aoe": "1 creature",
      "casting_time": "1 turn",
      "duration": "Special",
      "save": "Special",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "This spell is very much like the 5th-level wizard spell *sending*, allowing a brief contact with a far distant creature. However, with this spell the message can also contain a *suggestion* (see the 3rd-level wizard spell *suggestion*), which the subject will do its best to carry out if it **fails its saving throw vs. spell**, made with a **-2 penalty**.\n\nIf the message is **impossible or meaningless** according to the subject's current situation, it is understood, but **no saving throw is necessary** and the suggestion has no effect.\n\nThe caster must be **familiar with the creature contacted** and must know its **name and appearance well**.\n\n- If the creature is **not on the same plane of existence**, there is a base **5% chance the demand fails** to arrive.\n- Local conditions on other planes may worsen this chance, at the DM's discretion.\n\nIf the demand is received, it is understood even by creatures with **Intelligence as low as 1**. Creatures of **demigod status or higher** may choose to ignore the demand entirely.\n\nThe **demand message** must be **25 words or less**, including the suggestion. The creature may send back a **short reply immediately**.",
      "source": "Player's Handbook",
      "page": 240,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
