      "range": "0",
      "aoe": "1,000 square feet/level",
      "casting_time": "10 turns",
      "duration": "Permanent",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "This powerful spell allows a caster to transfer a **large area of land** in the Prime Material Plane to **any of the elemental planes**. All buildings, people, and wildlife within the area of effect are also transported.\n\nThe land forms a **pocket of the Prime Material** within the elemental plane:\n- The pocket is a **sphere** equal in diameter to the land area.\n- The **surface** allows creatures to pass, but blocks elemental intrusion.\n- Inside: normal air (matching the Prime Material at the moment of transfer) and a source of water.\n\nThe area must be **ringed by solid markers** made from material native to the destination plane, placed no more than five feet apart.\n\nThe wizard must be **within the area** during casting. Once moved, the land **cannot be moved again** using this spell.\n\nIf the **control device** (a magical item for commanding elementals) is disturbed, the spell **fails**, and elemental energies flood the pocket.\n\nThe control device is consumed in the casting and must be placed at the heart of the estate.",
      "source": "Tome of Magic",
      "page": 46,
      "reversible": false
