      "description": "A beam of **shimmering, kaleidoscopic light** shoots from the caster's fingertips toward a target.\n\n- Has **no effect** on non-spellcasters or creatures with innate spell-like abilities.\n- **Wizards and priests** may lose memorized spells.\n\n**Effect**:\n- The number of spells drained = *caster's level - 1d20*.\n- If the result is 0 or less, **no spells are lost**.\n- Lost spells are selected starting from **1st-level upward**, and chosen randomly.\n\nLost spells must be **rememorized**.",
