      "description": "### Homunculus Shield (Evocation, Necromancy)\n\nThe caster **externalizes a fragment of his mind** as a magical homunculus, which appears as a miniature version of the caster.\n\n- The caster can act normally while the homunculus casts **teleport, contingency, or protective spells (4th level or lower)**.\n- Spells are cast from the caster's memorized list and use **1-round casting time**.\n\n- The homunculus has **1 hit point per 2 caster levels**, reducing the caster’s own hit points.\n- It cannot be attacked separately but may be damaged by **area effects**.\n\nAt the end of the duration, the homunculus vanishes, and hit points may be restored only by **magical healing**.\n\nWhile active, the caster suffers a **-4 penalty to saving throws vs. magic jar**.",
