      "damage": "",
      "description": "This spell creates undead skeletons and zombies from the bones and bodies of dead animals, specifically vertebrates (fish, amphibians, reptiles, birds, and mammals). The animated remains obey simple verbal commands given by the caster, regardless of the language employed.\n\nOnly naturally occurring animals of no higher than semi-intelligence can be animated (e.g., cats, frogs, tigers), including giant-sized animals. These undead remain animated until destroyed in combat or turned; the animating magic cannot be dispelled.\n\n**Skeletons Created per Caster Level**:\n- 1/4 HD or less: 4\n- 1/2 to 1 HD: 2\n- 1+ to 3 HD: 1\n- 3+ to 6 HD: 1 per 2 levels\n- Over 6 HD: 1 per 4 levels\n\n**Zombies Created per Caster Level**:\n- 1/4 HD or less: 2\n- 1/2 to 1 HD: 1\n- 1 to 3 HD: 1 per 2 levels\n- Over 3 HD: 1 per 4 levels\n\nSkeletons and zombies gain standard undead immunities, lose special attacks, and have penalties to AC, damage, and movement. The material components are a blood drop and bone chip from the same species as the remains.",
