      "damage": "",
      "description": "This spell causes a target’s throat to constrict and lungs to swell shut, mimicking a deadly allergic reaction. Affected creatures must be within range and fail a saving throw vs. death magic.\n\nIf fewer than six creatures are targeted, they receive penalties to their save: –1 for 4–5, –2 for 2–3, –4 if only one is targeted.\n\nEach round, victims must roll a Constitution check:\n- Fail: 1d6 damage\n- Success: 1d3 damage\n\nVictims are **slowed** while struggling to breathe. Failure on **three consecutive Constitution checks** causes death on the following round.\n\nThe effect ends if the target leaves the area or if *dispel magic* is used. Slowed status persists 1–3 rounds afterward. Creatures that do not breathe (e.g., undead, plants) are immune.\n\nMaterial components: An unholy symbol and a symbolic silken gag wrapped around the caster’s mouth after casting.",
