      "description": "This spell affects only undead (not living creatures). It automatically immobilizes all **corporeal undead of 6 HD or less** (e.g., skeletons, ghouls, zombies) with **no saving throw**. They curl into a \"boneball\" of 2–3 feet per creature, held helpless with abilities suspended.\n\nThese undead can be rolled or moved into enemy areas and then released.\n\nFor **noncorporeal undead** or those of **7+ HD**, the spell works like *slow*, and such creatures get a **saving throw**. \"Special\" undead are unaffected.\n\nMaterial component: A bone held in the wizard’s left hand during casting.",
