      "description": "The caster touches a living creature’s head and attempts to destroy the brain through necromantic energy. A failed save causes **instant death** as the brain is effectively annihilated.\n\nCreatures immune to mind-affecting spells (like constructs or mindless undead) are unaffected. This spell has no effect on creatures without a discernible brain.\n\nThere is **no physical damage** visible from the outside, but the interior of the skull is reduced to mush. Raise dead is ineffective; resurrection or wish may be needed.",
