      "damage": "",
      "description": "This spell drives a victim insane. The DM may consult the madness table in Chapter Three or choose a form of insanity to suit the wicked caster.\n\nExamples include:\n- **Fear of dying**: Victim must save vs. paralyzation to resist a fear spell when seeing death imagery.\n- **Corpse paranoia**: Believes all corpses are undead, causing paranoia.\n- **Combat disablement**: Inflict *confusion* or *feeblemindedness* for quick neutralization.\n\n**The insanity is permanent** unless cured by *cure insanity* (reverse of this spell), *heal*, *restoration*, or *wish*.\n\n**Reverse effect**: *Cure insanity* restores sanity immediately (no save). It also:\n- Ends most magical, psionic, or poison-induced madness\n- Heals psychic trauma (e.g., from *mindwipe*)\n- Restores 5–40 PSPs\n- Temporarily calms some extraplanar madness (DM’s call)\n\nIt does **not** cure madness from lycanthropy, undeath, or powerful curses like *geas*【127:7†TSR 2151 - The Complete Book of Necromancers.pdf】.",
