      "description": "This spell transfers a recipient's life force into a **fresh corpse**, animating it like a puppet. While in control, the real body becomes paralyzed but remains aware. The caster or another touched target becomes the “master” of the corpse.\n\n- Range: 5 miles/level\n- Corpse retains HP equal to master's full total\n- Can speak hoarsely, fight, and perform most actions (except fine motor tasks)\n- Cannot pass for a living being without illusion magic\n\nThe caster may switch back at any time or is forced to if the corpse is destroyed or moved beyond range.\n\nIf the host dies:\n- A **system shock roll** is required or the caster dies\n- Can be severed by *dispel magic*, *wish*, or *spirit release*\n\n**Components**: A fresh corpse (dead ≤ 1 day per level) and a **fresh patch of the recipient’s skin**, which causes 1–3 hp damage and potentially permanent hp loss on failed save【127:8†TSR 2151 - The Complete Book of Necromancers.pdf】.",
