      "description": "Transfers damage from a touched target to the caster.\n\n- Max transfer: **2 hp/level**\n- Damage types: Physical, some poisons, disease, curse effects\n- Cannot restore lost limbs, life levels, or irreversible conditions\n- Only reverses harm temporarily if it's ongoing (e.g., poison continues)\n\nCaster may transfer up to current HP (or –9 if using “hovering on death’s door” rule).\n\nDM may allow this spell to act like *death's door* to stabilize the dying.\n\n**Damage is taken by the caster**, who may recover via rest or healing magic【127:16†TSR 2151 - The Complete Book of Necromancers.pdf】.",
