      "damage": "",
      "description": "This spell snuffs out the life forces of **small rodents and vermin**, such as flies, mice, beetles, rats, spiders, and similar pests. It only affects creatures with **1–3 hp per caster level** (maximum 9 hp) and **animal intelligence**.\n\n- If the creatures are extremely small (1 hp or less), the caster may affect **1 cubic foot per level**, up to 10 cubic feet.\n\nUseful both indoors and outdoors, the spell is favored by necromancers dealing with pestilence. Some evil mages misuse it on benign animals or pets.\n\n**Components**:\n- Somatic: Pointed finger\n- Verbal: Low “zzzt” sound\n- Material: Pinch of lavender and dried garlic【133:15†TSR 2151 - The Complete Book of Necromancers.pdf】.",
