      "damage": "",
      "description": "This spell targets the **heart of a living creature**, requiring line of sight. The caster must concentrate for **three rounds**. During that time, the caster may walk or talk but not cast spells or fight.\n\n- **1st round**: Victim saves vs. death magic at –2 (+Con modifier). Failure causes **1d8 damage** and incapacitates the target for 1 round.\n- **2nd round**: Another save at –1 (+Con mod). Failure causes:\n  - **25% HP loss**\n  - **2–5 rounds of paralysis**\n  - **2–5 point loss** each to Strength, Constitution, and Dexterity\n- **3rd round**: Final save (no penalty). Failure causes:\n  - **Immediate death** via heart attack\n  - Or **coma for 1–4 days** and permanent **–1 Constitution**\n\nThe spell ends early if line of sight is broken, the caster is disrupted, or the victim receives healing attention. The spell can be disrupted by *dispel magic*, *protection from evil*, or a *scarab of protection* (at cost of a charge)【133:10†TSR 2151 - The Complete Book of Necromancers.pdf】.",
