      "damage": "2d4 + 1d4 cold (AoE)",
      "description": "This spell fires a dagger of ice at the target. The caster makes a normal attack roll as if attacking with a missile weapon, factoring in the range (short: 10 yards, medium: 20 yards, long: 30 yards). A successful hit causes **2d4 hit points of damage**.\n\nIf the ice knife misses, consult grenade-like missile rules to determine its landing point. Upon striking a solid object or creature, it shatters, releasing **numbing cold** in a 5-foot radius. Affected creatures must save vs. paralyzation or take **1d4 cold damage** and be **numbed for 1–3 rounds**, reducing movement by half and attack rolls by –2. Proximity to intense heat grants a +2 bonus on the saving throw.\n\nThe ice knife cannot be reused. If touched, it shatters as described. Untouched knives melt away **1 round after creation**, regardless of temperature.",
      "source": "The Complete Wizard's Handbook",
      "page": "123",
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
