      "range": "10 yards/level",
      "aoe": "Caster",
      "casting_time": "3",
      "duration": "1 turn/level",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "The caster duplicates the **facial appearance** of another **human, demihuman, or humanoid** (not undead), so long as the subject is in range and visible.\n\nOnly the **face changes**—the caster retains their own voice, body, abilities, and senses. This is **not an illusion** and cannot be detected or dispelled by illusion-detecting magic. However, **dispel magic** will reverse the effect.\n\nThe spell serves as a potent magical disguise but **radiates necromantic magic** under detection.",
      "source": "The Complete Wizard's Handbook",
      "page": "123",
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 836,
      "name": "Hovering Skull",
      "level": "3",
      "school": "Necromancy",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": true,
      "somatic": true,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "The tooth from a human skull",
      "range": "Special",
      "aoe": "Special",
      "casting_time": "4",
      "duration": "2 rounds/level",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "1d6 bite",
      "description": "This spell creates a glowing human skull with sharp fangs. The skull hovers about a foot above the caster's shoulder; as the caster moves, the skull hovers along with him.\n\nIf the caster stops moving and concentrates, he can mentally command the hovering skull to move in any direction within a 30-foot radius. The caster can see through the skull’s eyes as if they were his own—useful for spying or scouting.\n\nThe caster may also command the skull to attack with its razor-sharp teeth, dealing 1d6 damage per bite. If concentration is interrupted, the skull falls harmlessly to the ground but can be controlled again once concentration resumes.\n\nThe skull shares the caster’s statistics except it has 3 hp and is independent of damage to or from the caster.",
      "source": "The Complete Wizard's Handbook",
      "page": "123",
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "id": 837,
      "name": "Iron Mind",
