      "duration": "1 turn/level",
      "save": "Neg.",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "Blackmantle surrounds the affected area with an aura that **negates all forms of healing and regeneration**, both magical and natural.\n\n- **Potions**, **spells**, and **regenerative effects** (e.g., trolls’ abilities or magical items like a *ring of regeneration*) cease to function.\n- **Used magic is wasted** during the effect.\n- Healing **resumes only after** the spell ends (but lost magic charges or potions are not restored).\n- A successful saving throw **negates the effect** for individual creatures.\n\nThis spell is especially potent when used to prevent recovery during or after combat.",
      "source": "The Complete Wizard's Handbook",
      "page": "124",
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Catapult",
      "level": "1",
      "id": 841,
      "school": "Alteration",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "",
      "range": "150 feet",
      "aoe": "One object",
      "casting_time": "1",
      "duration": "1 round",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "Weapon: +1 to hit; Small item: 2-3; Large item: 2-4",
      "description": "By means of this spell, the caster may cause any single item weighing 3 lbs. or less to move in a straight line in the direction pointed by the mage. The item will head off in that direction until it reaches the limit of the spell and then fall to the ground. The item must be loose or freestanding or not held by someone, and light enough to move (otherwise the item will quiver in place and the spell will be wasted).\n\nThis spell can be used offensively to hurl an item into an enemy. The item hits the individual in its path with the caster’s THAC0, with a +3 to the die. It is considered a +3 magical weapon when rolling to hit but not when rolling damage. The damage caused depends on the item, but use the following guidelines:\n\n| Item Type   | Damage                |\n|-------------|------------------------|\n| Weapon      | As weapon +1           |\n| Small item  | 2–3 points             |\n| Large item  | 2–4 points (2–3 lbs.)  |",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 44,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Corpselight",
      "level": "1",
      "id": 842,
      "school": "Alteration/Necromancy",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "Carrion, a pinch of saltpeter, bit of phosphorous or glowworm",
      "range": "10 yards/level",
      "aoe": "1 body/level",
      "casting_time": "1",
      "duration": "1 turn/level",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "This spell causes a dead or undead body to glow with a pale radiance. The glow may be white, yellow, green, amber, or red according to the desire of the caster. The caster may alter the glow at will, provided he is within 30 feet of the glowing body. The light may vary from the barest outline to the brightness of a torch, suitable for reading or detailed work.\n\nThe glow is diffuse and constant, and does not penalize the undead figure in combat (cf *faerie fire*). The caster can affect one medium-sized body per level, twice as many small-sized bodies, half as many large-sized bodies, and one-fourth that many huge creatures. Nothing that is larger than huge can be affected by this spell. The glow does not harm undead creatures in any way. It can be cast on undead which have material form, even if that form is gaseous (such as wraiths, but excluding ghosts, which exist primarily on other planes).\n\nThis spell can be used by necromancers (specialist mages in necromancy) but not by transmuters (specialist mages in alteration magic).",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 44,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Know School",
      "level": "1",
      "id": 843,
      "school": "Divination",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "Small tube of paper or vellum",
      "range": "120 yards",
      "aoe": "1 target",
      "casting_time": "1",
      "duration": "1 round",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "By means of this spell the caster may determine the school of another spellcaster (if any). This spell will only function on other wizards who are specialist mages in a particular area (abjurers, conjurers, necromancers, etc.). The spell produces no result on priests, spellcasters without schools, or creatures without spell ability.\n\nThis spell is used primarily to vouch for the statements of one particular wizard as a spellcaster of one particular type or another. The target is unaware of being divined upon, but as with all such divination spells, probably would take umbrage if he found out. Let the caster beware.",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 44,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Scatterspray",
      "level": "1",
      "id": 844,
      "school": "Alteration",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "The items and flint and steel or tinderbox",
      "range": "10 yards/level",
      "aoe": "10 foot radius",
      "casting_time": "1",
      "duration": "1 round",
      "save": "Neg.",
      "damage": "Size S: 1d6; Size M: 1d4; Size L+: none",
      "description": "Upon casting this spell, the mage can point to any collection of small, unsecured items grouped together within the spell’s range and cause them to fly off in all directions simultaneously. The items will fly 10 feet in random directions, rebound against the limits of the spell and bounce around inside the area of effect for one round, damaging those caught in the area.\n\nNo less than six items or more than 14 can be affected. The items can be no larger than chicken eggs and are typically such things as coins, marbles, gems, dice, or sling bullets. Items which are in pouches or otherwise restrained are not affected, though those in an open pouch could be enchanted by this spell.\n\nCreatures of size S generally take 1–6 points of damage from the shrapnel while those of size M take 1–4 and those of size L and larger are unharmed. A successful save vs. spells negates the damage. Small creatures flying into a scatterspray must save vs. spells or be grounded, unable to fly, for 1–4 turns. Size M or larger flying creatures are unharmed. Magical protection such as *shield*, *wall of force*, *Bigby’s hands*, and *protection from normal missiles* will protect those within from the effects of the scatterspray. The caster is always unharmed by the scatterspray, even if within its area of effect.\n\nThe damage from scatterspray assumes hard objects are used for missiles. Eggs, fruit, and other soft objects can be used, but this reduces damage by 2 points in all cases (down to a minimum of 0). Spellcasting is not possible from inside a scatterspray if the spell-casting opponent fails a saving throw vs. spells.",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 44,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Bind",
      "level": "2",
      "id": 845,
      "school": "Enchantment",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "",
      "range": "30 yards",
      "aoe": "50 ft. + 5 ft./level",
      "casting_time": "2",
      "duration": "1 round/level",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "When this spell is cast, the wizard causes all loose cloth or rope-like items within the area of effect to act as if animated. The spell causes these items to lash about wildly for one round, then attempt to bind any moving creature within reach for the remainder of the duration.\n\nThe material used may be of any composition (silk, wool, hemp, leather, etc.). The bindings strike with THAC0 15 and if successful, entangle the creature for the rest of the spell duration, unless it makes a successful Strength check each round. Any victim who breaks free early is not re-attacked.\n\nThe material used does not gain increased strength or hardness. It can be burned, cut, or broken. If there is no material in the area, the spell fails. If the caster is within the area, he is unaffected.",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 58,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Blacklight",
      "level": "2",
      "id": 846,
      "school": "Alteration",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "Piece of coal and the dried eyeball of any creature",
      "range": "10 yards/level",
      "aoe": "20-foot-radius globe",
      "casting_time": "3",
      "duration": "1 round/level",
      "save": "Neg.",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "Upon casting this spell, the wizard creates a stationary, temporary area of total darkness. The darkness is impenetrable to normal vision and infravision, but the caster can see and move normally within the blacklit area. The caster can attack and cast spells normally within the limits of his blacklight.\n\nEach round, those within the blacklit area are allowed a saving throw vs. spells at –3. Those who succeed can see as the wizard does for that round, while those who fail are wrapped in total darkness. Characters outside the sphere cannot see into it.\n\nNormal and magical lights are doused by the blacklight. The casting of *light*, *continual light*, or *dispel magic* will destroy the blacklit area. The caster of blacklight can end the spell at will, though continual concentration is not necessary to maintain it. Spells which depend on visual effects (such as illusions) do not function if the victim cannot see them.",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 47,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Dispel Silence",
      "level": "2",
      "id": 847,
      "school": "Abjuration/Alteration",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "Pinch of powdered diamond worth at least 50 gp",
      "range": "0",
      "aoe": "10-foot-radius sphere/level",
      "casting_time": "3",
      "duration": "1 round/level",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "This spell negates the effect of magical silence within the area of the *dispel silence* spell for the duration of the spell. Following the casting of the *dispel silence*, all spell-casting, speaking, and actions can proceed normally.\n\nFor the duration of the spell, the area protected by the *dispel silence* is proof against silence spells—they will not function within the area of the *dispel silence*. The area is immovable, however, and does not follow the caster around.",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 47,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Ghost Armor",
      "level": "2",
      "id": 848,
      "school": "Conjuration",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "Fragment of real armor worn in battle",
      "range": "Touch",
      "aoe": "1 creature, size H or smaller",
      "casting_time": "1",
      "duration": "1 round/level",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "This spell creates a suit of magical armor around the caster or a touched creature. This armor is weightless, noiseless, and does not restrict movement. It provides AC 3 protection (or improves the target’s AC to 3, if worse). The armor is invisible, and does not interfere with spellcasting, thieving, or other actions.\n\nIt is considered a force effect, not physical armor, and therefore is unaffected by spells like *heat metal* or attacks from rust monsters. It remains for 1 round per level or until dispelled.",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 48,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Mindnet",
      "level": "2",
      "id": 849,
      "school": "Divination, Enchantment/Charm",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "",
      "range": "0",
      "aoe": "Special",
      "casting_time": "1 round/2 participants",
      "duration": "12 turns",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "This spell links the minds of up to four individuals (including the caster), allowing them to share limited thoughts and perceptions. All must be willing participants. The spell requires 1 round of casting per participant. Once established, the group shares telepathic communication, with full awareness of each other’s physical status, emotions, and immediate surroundings.\n\nIn addition, once per turn, the caster may teleport one participant instantly to the location of another, provided both are part of the mindnet. The caster must make a Constitution check at the end of each turn to maintain the link; failure ends the spell prematurely. The spell ends automatically after 12 turns or if the caster ceases concentration.",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 50,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Snilloc’s Snowball",
      "level": "2",
      "id": 850,
      "school": "Evocation",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "Chunk of ice or a small bit of ivory",
      "range": "20 yards/level",
      "aoe": "One target or creature",
      "casting_time": "1",
      "duration": "Instantaneous",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "1d3 (or 1d6 vs fire-using/fire-dwelling creatures)",
      "description": "This spell creates a mystical snowball in the hand of the caster which can then be thrown immediately against any target within range. The snowball hits automatically for 1–3 points of damage, 1–6 points if used against a fire-using or fire-dwelling opponent. The snowball strikes like a *magic missile* and can be affected and repelled in the same way (*brooch of shielding*, *thunderlance*, etc.).\n\n*Snilloc’s Snowball* is considered by most mages to be a lesser form of *magic missile*, though it has the advantage in range at higher levels (as opposed to multiple strikes) and can be directed against an object as well as a creature. It is also more effective against fiery creatures.\n\nThere are reports of a 2nd-level variant of this spell with identical effects called *Snilloc’s Cream Pie*. These reports are unconfirmed.",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 48,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Spectral Senses",
      "level": "2",
      "id": 851,
      "school": "Divination",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "A drop of ink and a scrap of cloth",
      "range": "Touch",
      "aoe": "One creature",
      "casting_time": "3",
      "duration": "1 hour/level",
      "save": "None",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "The recipient of this spell gains spectral sensory powers, enabling them to see invisible or ethereal creatures and objects, hear distant whispers clearly, and sense magical emanations in the area. These abilities do not require active concentration.\n\nThe spell lasts 1 hour per caster level. It does not reveal illusions or phantasms, but allows detection of creatures hidden by non-illusion-based concealment. The recipient can also automatically detect the presence of undead or constructs within 30 feet, though not their exact location or type.",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 48,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Unluck",
      "level": "2",
      "id": 852,
      "school": "Evocation",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "Piece of a broken mirror",
      "range": "10 yards",
      "aoe": "One creature",
      "casting_time": "4",
      "duration": "2d10 rounds",
      "save": "Neg.",
      "damage": "",
      "description": "With this spell, the wild mage creates a negative pattern in the random forces surrounding one creature. The creature is allowed a saving throw; if successful, the spell fails. If the saving throw is failed, random chance falls into an unlucky pattern. Any action involving random chance (i.e., any time a die roll affects the character) performed by the victim during the next 2–20 rounds requires two separate attempts; the worse result is always applied. (The victim rolls twice for attacks, damages, saving throws, etc., always using the worse die roll.)\n\nA luckstone or similar magical device will negate unluck. Doing so, however, prevents the magical item from functioning for 2d10 rounds. The material component is a piece of a broken mirror.",
      "source": "Forgotten Realms Adventures",
      "page": 49,
      "reversible": false
    },
    {
      "name": "Dire Charm",
      "level": "3",
      "id": 853,
      "school": "Enchantment/Charm",
      "caster": "wizard",
      "verbal": false,
      "somatic": false,
      "material": false,
      "materials": "",
      "range": "120 yards",
      "aoe": "One individual",
      "casting_time": "3",
      "duration": "1-4 rounds + 1 round/level",
